pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator agent. You will receive the move lists from three agents (some may be 'no_moves'). Your objective is to:
1) Validate and, if necessary, reorder or request clarification to ensure the combined move sequence is legal under Tower of Hanoi rules and agent permissions.
2) Produce a PDDL domain and a PDDL problem suitable for the FastDownward planner that encodes the multi-agent actions and the global goal. Enclose the PDDL domain between <domain></domain> and the PDDL problem between <problem></problem>.
3) Emit a consolidated ordered list of primitive moves (one per line) in the exact format 'agent_i: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'.

Here are the agents' reported move lists:
{moves_agent_1}
{moves_agent_2}
{moves_agent_3}

Public information to respect:
{environment->public_information}

Keep actions for different agents distinct in the PDDL. Target the FastDownward solver (use STRIPS-style predicates and actions compatible with FastDownward). If you detect any illegal move or permission violation in the agents' lists, correct the sequence and document the correction in the PDDL problem comments and in the consolidated move list. Finally, provide the PDDL domain and problem and the consolidated move list.
